  "text": "Based on the 0099 trial, [CITATION_1] concurrent chemoradiation with or without adjuvant chemotherapy was the current standard care for locoregionally advanced NPC. Baujat et al. [CITATION_2] also demonstrated a significant increase of concurrent chemotherapy for both OS (6% at 5 years) and PFS (10% at 5 years) rates. However, the acute toxicities stopped many patients from completing the whole therapy. In our study, 74.67% patients discontinued concurrent chemotherapy mainly due to intolerable toxicities.",
